Package: netaipq
Title: Networks and Machine Learning for 'phyloseq' Objects
Version: 0.1.0.9000
Authors@R:
    person("Adrien", "Taudière", , "adrien.taudiere@zaclys.net", role = c("aut", "cre", "cph"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0003-1088-1182"))
Description: Network, graph, causal-inference, and machine-learning tools
    for 'phyloseq' objects within the 'pqverse' ecosystem. Provides
    genuinely new analysis methods (co-occurrence and association
    networks, bipartite-network visualisation, supervised classification,
    indicator-species and differential-abundance analyses) that go beyond
    simple 'ggplot2' wrappers. 'netaipq' is the home for any item adding a
    brand-new machine-learning, network, graph, or statistical-analysis
    dependency, keeping 'MiscMetabar' lean. Built on top of 'MiscMetabar'.
License: AGPL-3
URL: https://adrientaudiere.github.io/netaipq/,
    https://github.com/adrientaudiere/netaipq
BugReports: https://github.com/adrientaudiere/netaipq/issues
